@*
    Shared structured dietary / allergy capture (REQUIREMENTS §21 Participant [H]).

    Renders, for the bound DietaryInput:
      - a diet-lifestyle dropdown (None / Vegetarian / Vegan / …),
      - a fieldset of the 14 common EU allergens as checkboxes (a11y: fieldset +
        legend groups them for screen readers; each checkbox has its own <label>),
      - a free-text "other" box for the long tail.

    Used identically on /Forms/Dinner and /Forms/Speaker so structured catering
    data is captured the same way on both. Mobile-first: the allergen grid wraps
    to a single column at ~360px. The checkbox field name == the entity property
    name == the aggregation key (see DietaryInput / DietaryAggregator).

    HOW TO USE (in a form, with a [BindProperty] public DietaryInput Dietary):
        <partial name="_DietaryFieldset" model="Model.Dietary" />
*@
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Localization
@using CommunityHub.Core.Domain
@inject IHtmlLocalizer<CommunityHub.Core.Resources.SharedResource> Localizer
@model CommunityHub.Pages.Shared.DietaryInput

<style>
    /* Allergen checkbox grid — two columns on a phone-friendly width, single
       column under ~360px. Scoped class names; no global override. */
    .ceh-diet-allergens {
        display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 4px 18px;
        margin: 6px 0 12px; padding: 0; border: 0;
    }
    .ceh-diet-allergens label {
        display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;
        font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; margin: 2px 0;
    }
    .ceh-diet-allergens input[type=checkbox] { width: auto; margin: 0; }
    @@media (max-width: 380px) {
        .ceh-diet-allergens { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
</style>

<label for="Dietary_DietChoice">@Localizer["Diet.DietChoiceLabel"]</label>
@* The "None" choice already renders as "No special diet" (the default), so the empty
   "-- no special diet --" placeholder was a confusing duplicate and is removed. *@
<select asp-for="DietChoice" id="Dietary_DietChoice" name="Dietary.DietChoice">
    @foreach (var choice in DietaryRequirement.DietChoices)
    {
        <option value="@choice">@Localizer[$"Diet.Choice.{choice}"]</option>
    }
</select>

@* The 14-allergen "tick all that apply" checkbox grid was removed (operator 2026-06-28);
   the diet dropdown + the free-text box below capture dietary needs. The allergen columns
   remain on DietaryInput (unset) so persisted data + the aggregator are unaffected. *@

<label for="Dietary_OtherAllergens">@Localizer["Diet.OtherLabel"]</label>
<textarea id="Dietary_OtherAllergens" name="Dietary.OtherAllergens" rows="2"
          placeholder="@Localizer["Diet.OtherPlaceholder"]">@Model.OtherAllergens</textarea>
